Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.88,0:32:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In a dualistic world, one wins and the\Nother one loses.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.20,0:32:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's from materialistic linear\Nperception.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.84,0:32:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Karmically, a loss may be the biggest\Ngain of your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.27,0:32:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the world is what it is. It's\Nthe optimum theater for karmic benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.00,0:32:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the optimum place for the undoing\Nof negative karma and the gaining of
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.36,0:32:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,positive karma. Therefore, wanting to\Nchange the world doesn't make much
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.24,0:32:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,sense. You know, Ramanar, she says,\N"The world you see doesn't even exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.67,0:33:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Save yourself the trouble and surrender\Nit to God. So if the purpose of the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.39,0:33:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,world is to provide an optimum\Nopportunity for the undoing of negative
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.96,0:33:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,karma,\Nall your dogooderism is going to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.76,0:33:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,sentence those people to a continuation\Nof bad karma. Is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.64,0:33:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't kill themselves on the street\Ncar. They'll do it on the bus. They'll
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.67,0:33:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,drive off.\NOh Lord. So
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.88,0:33:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,all right, win and lose is the ego's\Nperception because you don't know uh
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.48,0:33:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,what seeming loss is going to be a\Ntremendous gain. Mhm. You don't know
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.20,0:33:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,what's seeming loss is is going to open\Nthe door. So it's by loss that the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.96,0:33:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,doorway to the new is open because\Notherwise the ego is going to constantly
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.55,0:33:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,cling to the past. It's going to cling\Nto the familiar and we'll never know
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.55,0:33:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,what freedom is like. Huh?\Nuh importance the idea that you have to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.55,0:34:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,be important and here you might be\Nnobody see uh you got to be noticed and
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.12,0:34:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,uh that's the whole world of glamour to\Nbe noticed and so the basic here thing
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.72,0:34:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,about the ego which has been ever since\Nthe beginning of time is it constantly
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.76,0:34:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,seeks for gain and its fear is one of\Nloss it clutches
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.11,0:34:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so the ego is characterized by\Nclutchingness it wants to control.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.00,0:34:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the minute the ego thinks a thing\Nis mine, it totally changes dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.39,0:34:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,H the magic of mine instantly changes\Nit.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.59,0:34:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just a watch.\NBut if it's my watch, uh-oh, now it's
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.87,0:34:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,special.\NNow it's my sentimental watch. Now it's
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.00,0:34:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,old granddad's watch.\NOh wow. Now it began it's ego you know
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.24,0:34:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it's ego inflation\Nthe minute you add mind. Therefore the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.04,0:35:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,body should be referred to as an it.\NWhatever it's doing is really not all
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.72,0:35:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that interesting if you watch it. It\Nit does what it's supposed to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.07,0:35:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And when the ego sort of resolves into\Njust sort of a oneness, uh you watch it
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.59,0:35:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,walking around and it's like a windup\Ntoy. You see it's still you still doing
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.00,0:35:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it\Nfor decades. It just wander. It walks
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.11,0:35:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,around by itself.\NDoes whatever it's going to do. It
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.80,0:35:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,points with this thing.\NI mean it's a marvelous mechanism. I
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.83,0:35:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,don't want anything to do with it. But\Nthere it goes on its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.16,0:35:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Win and lose importance the idea. So if\Nyou say my body
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.32,0:35:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,or my mind, my possessions, my the\Nminute you add the word my, you're
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.20,0:35:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,stuck.\NFirst of all, nothing belongs to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.28,0:36:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.\NEverything belongs to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.83,0:36:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You have temporary custody.\NTemporary custody. Yeah. You are the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.59,0:36:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,steward of these things.\NSee yourself as the steward rather than
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.32,0:36:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the owner.\NIt's the body and it's the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.64,0:36:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you stop referring to it as me,\Nit loses its attractive ego investment.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.16,0:36:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a body and it's the body and it's\Nthe mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.11,0:36:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, to be hypnotized by the mind is to\Nthink these are my thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.32,0:36:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The thoughts emanate from the field of\Nconsciousness impersonally.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.40,0:36:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you connect with a certain\Nlevel of consciousness, you're connected
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.24,0:36:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to an attractor field. That attractor\Nfield has the same thoughts and has
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.80,0:37:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,always had them,\Nyou know, for thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.64,0:37:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing novel about it. It's\Nmine and I'll kill you. You think that's
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.32,0:37:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,your thought?\NDid you invent that thought? Something
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.32,0:37:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,new in man's history.\NThat prevailing thought field thinks
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.96,0:37:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that way. Those thoughts belong to the\Nfield they're not yours. So don't claim
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.44,0:37:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,ownership for that which over over which\Nyou have no ownership.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.11,0:37:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing belongs to anyone.\NEverything belongs to divinity. You have
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.04,0:37:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,temporary custody. temporary\Nstewardship.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.64,0:37:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So to give up your life for something\Nwhich isn't even yours is a little
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.32,0:37:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,ridiculous, you know.\NOh lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.88,0:37:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So the importance then is uh this is\Nself-importance.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.16,0:38:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So the ego is designed to gain uh money\Nof course is a very big one. Money,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.16,0:38:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,excitement, all these things are very\Nbig.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.59,0:38:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,When we get to the levels of\Nconsciousness correlating with
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.48,0:38:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,happiness, you will notice that\Nhappiness is almost one to one
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.72,0:38:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,correlated with level of consciousness\Nand with nothing else.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.56,0:38:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Does not correlate with wealth. Not even\Ncorrelated with health. Not correlated
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.20,0:38:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,with success. It's correlated with level\Nof consciousness. Period.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.24,0:38:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Period. Yeah. So just advance your\Nconsciousness and think of all the work
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.40,0:38:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you save yourself.\NI mean, you know, you can be delighted
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.00,0:38:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,with nothing.\NThe less you got, the better. You can
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.92,0:38:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,live with a cot, a blanket you got from\Nthe Goodwill, a box, an apple, and a
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.40,0:39:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,six-pack, a pep.\NAnd to add to to your heavenly abode,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.40,0:39:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you get a cat. Yeah. So now you got\Neverything. You get a piece of cheese,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.32,0:39:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,some Pepsi, a cat, a cot, and uh a\Ncandle. There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.00,0:39:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Do you need anything to read? No. Do you\Nneed television? No. Do you need a
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.07,0:39:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,radio? No. Do you need to read the\Npaper? No.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.40,0:39:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't even know Regan had been shot\Nfor weeks later.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.80,0:39:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,In coffee shops I mention reg.\NAll right. So the ego is invested in in
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.83,0:39:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in all these various levels with being\Nimportant being noticed with gain. It
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.35,0:40:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,fears loss and money is the magical road\Nto happiness. Money
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.04,0:40:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The experiencer in order to justify its\Nown existence seeks the energy that it
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.28,0:40:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,pulls out of excitement and it dreads\Nboredom. Dreads boredom.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.52,0:40:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The way out of boredom is to allow\Nyourself to be bored and investigate why
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.04,0:40:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you feel bored and what that emotion is.\NIf you want to discover what the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.35,0:40:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,experiencer does,\Nallow yourself to instead of escapism,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.96,0:40:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,allow yourself to be bored and just\Ncontemplate
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.04,0:40:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,on what is boredom and what is it I'm\Nexperiencing and why do I have an
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.76,0:40:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,aversion to it?\NThat's a very rapid way to find out
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.32,0:40:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly what the experiencer is, what it\Ndoes, and what it observes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.92,0:40:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What is and then you say, well, what is\Nit that's bored?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.64,0:41:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What what is it? What aspect of myself\Nis it that's bored and complaining and
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.92,0:41:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,what is it complaining of? There's\Nnothing interesting going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.31,0:41:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What do I get out of interest?\NWhat do I get out of things that are
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.11,0:41:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,interesting?\Na sense of aliveness and excitement of
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.68,0:41:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the spirit or of the ego. Uhhuh. So you\Nsee
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.20,0:41:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the animal\Nwanting constant entertainment.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.72,0:41:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. It likes excitement and it\Ndreads boredom because boredom is almost
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.96,0:41:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,like death. It works off desire and it\Nhas afraid fears it won't get. It looks
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.76,0:41:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,for status and fears being a nobody. It\Nwants to be noticed and is afraid it'll
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.68,0:41:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,be ignored.\NIt wants to express its opinions about
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.24,0:41:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,everything and it dreads just being\Nordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.80,0:42:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Free speech is\Ncircus. Yeah. I had a good friend I knew
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.48,0:42:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,for many years and he came to me one day\Nand he said, "I just made the most
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.72,0:42:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,amazing discovery." I said, "What is\Nit?" He says I don't have to have an
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.80,0:42:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,opinion on everything.\NHe said, 'I never experienced such
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.04,0:42:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,freedom. You I no I don't have a view\Nhave to have a viewpoint. I don't have
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.35,0:42:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to have an opinion. I don't feel called\Nupon to express my free speech, take a
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.76,0:42:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,stand and get out there with a plaque\Ncard.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.92,0:42:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh so it was freedom.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.92,0:42:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Not. You don't have to have an opinion.\NAnd it's okay to be ordinary. It's okay
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.04,0:42:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to be ordinary.\NIn fact, it's really good to be ordinary
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.88,0:42:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,for when they're looking for who to\Nshoot. It this pays off.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.31,0:43:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, you said you with the pink\Nmustache and the red hair standing on.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.31,0:43:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Come over here, you son of\NNo, you want to blend in. My My survival
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.11,0:43:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,technique when I was young was to blend\Nin with the woodwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.00,0:43:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Blend in with the woodwork.\NIn boot camp, it's below zero in Great
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.72,0:43:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Lakes, pitch black in the morning. They\Nget you all up. You got to run around
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.48,0:43:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the the the thing a lap, a mile.\NNo breakfast, nothing in the black at
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.31,0:43:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Timber.\NSo I discovered the way to do is just
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.40,0:43:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,blend in, not be noticed. And they had\Nlockers and you could open the locker
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.40,0:43:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and as they went out.\NI did that all through boot camp.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.35,0:44:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You just blend in. They'll never notice\Nyou. See, if they notice you, they would
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.80,0:44:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,be out in the field and they'd say,\N"Where's Hawkins?" You know. No, by
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.88,0:44:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,being anonymous, he never noticed it.\NOne time I did get caught and I had to
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.04,0:44:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,do two laps around. But but most almost\Nthe whole time except that once
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.31,0:44:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the way to survive is to become\Ninvisible. See, that's the value of
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.64,0:44:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,camouflage.\NSo, if you're aggressive, you stand out
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.00,0:44:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,there and you avoid an aggression. See?\NAnd if you're good, well camouflaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.72,0:44:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I'd like to be an octopus. If\NI was going to be something, you just
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.31,0:44:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,like look like everything else around\Nyou.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.88,0:44:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All right?\NSo, we seek status. We want to be
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.72,0:44:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,noticed. We want to have an opinion. The\Nego is constantly craving things. And it
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.31,0:44:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,dreads frustration. It dreads not having\Nit. And therefore, to achieve all of the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.76,0:44:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,above, it wants control. It wants\Ncontrol.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.48,0:45:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And it has an aversion to accepting.\NIt wants to control the world and
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.56,0:45:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,control out there instead of\Nchange the world instead of changing
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.48,0:45:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself.\NIf you don't like the world the way it
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.56,0:45:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,is,\Nthen change yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.83,0:45:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Do the world a favor.\NAll the wondrous dogooders, the great
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.56,0:45:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,monarchs, the great rulers, all the\Ndogooders are dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.80,0:45:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Their dynasties are dead\Nto establish the greatest nation on
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.59,0:45:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,earth. They're all dead. They're all\Ndead.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.96,0:45:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All dead.\NInstead of changing the world, change
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.88,0:45:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself.\NIf the word God over the courthouse
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.80,0:45:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,makes you uncomfortable,\Nthen change yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.11,0:46:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would it make you uncomfortable? And\Nwhat do you care?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.16,0:46:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There's always protesters out about some\Nissue that doesn't even involve their
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.40,0:46:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,life. It's all in their head, you know.\NAll in their head.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.68,0:46:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh god. So it craves and what it wants\Nis control. So the one of the biggest
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.76,0:46:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,surreners you can make is letting go,\Nwanting to control things. Letting go,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.96,0:46:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,wanting to control because evolution is\Nevolving in a certain way. And therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.68,0:46:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to try and control it, you don't even\Nknow what you're asking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.92,0:46:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you're grabbing onto a high\Nvoltage wire when the minute you try to
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.35,0:46:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,control things. And the karmic\Nconsequences are so the best wisdom is
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.68,0:46:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to surrender it to God as surrender the\Nworld to God. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.83,0:46:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego doesn't like that. The spiritual\Nego wants to save the world. Save the
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.52,0:47:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,world.\NWhat are you going to save it from?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.28,0:47:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,from what\Nthe Buddha
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.44,0:47:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ all the great avatars\NSocrates
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.20,0:47:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,said the only problem that that exists\Nin the world is ignorance so if you're
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.68,0:47:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,going to sol do anything for the world\Nall you could do is try to o to educate
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.96,0:47:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and overcome ignorance huh the world you\Nsee doesn't even exist see you see it as
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.00,0:47:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,injustices\Nand that's from your position You see
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.28,0:47:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,there's an injustice from this position\Nover here. It is justice.
